---

## Changes

### 1. Merge keypad + calorieEntryDisplay + additionalLoggingDetails → calorieInput

These three are exclusively wired together in main.js to form the single calorie entry
input group. calorieEntryDisplay and additionalLoggingDetails have zero domain, application,
or infrastructure layers — they are pure UI children of the keypad-driven input flow with
no independent consumers.

### 2. Extract shared database → src/shared/infrastructure/db/

dexieDb.js defines the single Dexie instance with tables for both calories (calLog,
CaloriesLog) and settings (userSettings). It currently lives in calories/infrastructure/db/
but SettingsRepository imports it cross-feature. This is the app's single database — it
belongs in shared infrastructure.

### 3. Absorb today into appHeader

today.js exports 2 functions (getTodayDate, onDateChange). Its sole consumer is
appHeader.js. It has no domain, persistence, or UI of its own. Renamed to dateWatch.js
for clarity.

### 4. Extract shared icon assets → src/shared/assets/icons/

back.svg lives in aboutPage/components/ but is imported by showLog too. settings.svg is
in settings/components/. Shared assets shouldn't live inside a single feature.

### 5. No change needed

calories, miniDailyDash, showLog, settings, aboutPage, appHeader — these have distinct
responsibilities and stay as-is (with import path updates only).

